Description:
Substance/Radiance est à la recherche d’un(e) stagiaire en comptabilité à temps plein (possibilité d'emploi à temps partiel durant les études universitaires) pour compléter l'équipe finances et administration. Il s’agit d’un emploi idéal pour une personne dynamique et débrouillarde recherchant un environnement de travail agréable.
Description du poste:
Occuper un rôle actif dans le processus de facturation;
Travailler en étroite collaboration avec l'équipe de gestion;
Consigner dans un registre informatique les transactions comptables quotidiennes;
Gérer le cycle comptable des comptes fournisseurs;
Assurer un suivi au niveau du recouvrement des comptes clients;
Concilier les dépôts quotidiens;
Concilier les cartes de crédits;
Préparer les soumissions des rapports gouvernementaux (DAS, GST, QST);
Appuyer les divers projets spéciaux et participer à l’amélioration des processus de l’entreprise;
Effectuer d’autres tâches de bureau connexes (classement, traitement de texte, etc.).
Compétences professionnelles:
Aptitude à travailler en équipe;
Rigueur, autonomie et débrouillardise;
Capacité d’évoluer dans un domaine en mouvement/croissance;
Bonne tolérance au stress.
Exigences:
DEP, DEC/AEC ou certificat en comptabilité ou expérience dans un poste similaire;
Bonne connaissance de la suite Google, un atout;
Connaissance du logiciel XERO, un atout;
Maîtrise du français et de l’anglais, tant à l’oral qu’à l’écrit.
Envoie-nous ton CV et découvre pourquoi nous faisons partie du top 50 des entreprises certifiées Great Place To Work au Canada.

First Capital [TSX: FCR.UN] is a leading owner, operator, and developer of mixed-use real estate located in Canada’s most densely populated cities. First Capital’s focus is on creating thriving urban neighbourhoods to generate value for businesses, residents, communities and our investors. We strive for performance excellence at our properties and new developments, creating healthy and sustainable urban neighbourhoods. As one of the Greater Toronto Area’s top employers, we foster a vibrant corporate culture that ensures equal opportunity and well-being for all employees in a dynamic and rewarding workplace.
SUMMARY:
The Financial Analyst is responsible for providing support to the Finance, Treasury and Investor Relations Department.
PRIMARY RESPONSIBILITIES:
Treasury:
Assist in daily cash management and other treasury functions;
Monitor corporate bank accounts (including opening and closing bank accounts);
Prepare and process wires, and code invoices;
Assist in the preparation of quarterly reporting deliverables related to Treasury;
Prepare loan renewal notices by coordinating signatures internally and delivering to external parties;
Perform ad hoc tasks as required.
Finance:
Assist with the Financing process (equity, mortgages, unsecured debentures, credit facilities, etc);
Coordinate and liaise with various departments such as Accounting and Legal on administrative financing matters such as AML/KYC and ownership structures;
Maintain and organize documents and electronic files.
Investor Relations:
Assist in updating Investor Relations slides on a quarterly basis;
Update and maintain the investor database;
Monitor and track changes to company units and unitholders;
Complete retail REIT peer research, for industry comparison.
KNOWLEDGE, EXPERIENCE AND SKILLS:
Required level of education and job-related experience:
Diploma or Degree in business, finance or accounting with at least 1-2 years of related experience, preferably in a public company
Specific Skills
Strong administrative and organizational skills with keen attention to detail and accuracy;
Working knowledge of MS Outlook, Word, PowerPoint and proficiency in Excel;
Ability to communicate effectively, in both oral and written format;
Ability to allocate time effectively, work well under pressure, and manage tight deadlines;
Analytical, willing to challenge the status quo, and open to learning new things;
Commercial real estate experience preferable.
